<paragraph id="8B993694B840FF9CFF25FE08FEFEFD6E" blockId="6.[136,1452,411,690]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">
Herbs perennial. Root fibrous. Sterile stems erect, 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFD62FE08FCE5FE6A" box="[719,818,411,438]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“20 cm</quantity>
tall. Flowering stems erect or slightly bent, 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFA9EFE08FA7FFE6A" box="[1331,1448,411,437]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="cm" value="20.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“30 cm</quantity>
. Leaves 3-verticillate, leaf blade linear-lanceolate, 10â€“25 Ã— 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFC9AFE2CFC4DFE06" box="[823,922,447,473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2â€“3 mm</quantity>
, apex sub-acute, base shortly spurred, mostly 3-lobed, middle tilted 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFE27FE70FE06FE22" box="[394,465,483,509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
. Cyme 3â€“4 branched, corymbiform, ca. 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFC09FE70FC2EFE22" box="[932,1017,483,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“7 cm</quantity>
in diameter, many flowered. Flowers sessile except the central flower (
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFDBEFD94FDA1FDFE" box="[531,630,519,546]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“5 mm</quantity>
long), unequally 5-merous; bracts resembling stem leaves, 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFA98FD94FA70FDFE" box="[1333,1447,519,546]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“15 mm</quantity>
. Sepals linear-lanceolate, base shortly spurred, ca. 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFD6CFDB8FCF4FD9A" box="[705,803,555,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“6 mm</quantity>
, apex subacute. Petals yellow, narrowly ovate or broadly lanceolate, 4â€“7 Ã— 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFEF9FDDCFE62FDB6" box="[340,437,591,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“2 mm</quantity>
, apex acute, 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFDE5FDDCFD02FDB6" box="[584,725,591,618]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.2">0.2â€“0.5 mm</quantity>
. Stamens 10, 4â€“ 
<quantity id="4CDE9B71B840FF9CFC3DFDDCFC03FDB6" box="[912,980,591,618]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
; antepetalous ones ca. 
